question: In which year was the National Agricultural Cooperative Marketing Federation of India Ltd (NAFED) established?
explanation: National Agricultural Cooperative Marketing Federation of India Ltd (NAFED) is an apex organization of marketing cooperatives for agricultural produce in India, under the Ministry of Agriculture, Government of India. It was founded on the birthday of Mahatma Gandhi on 2 October 1958 to promote the trade of agricultural produce and forest resources across the nation. NAFED headquarters in New Delhi.
